Not alot of flavour, quite bland. I thought that the sherry would add a bit of a punch, but this recipe lacked flavour. Other than adding a can of diced tomatoes, I followed the recipe to the letter. I will not be making again. This recipe also makes a huge amount of soup, and took a very long time to cook. In the end, it totally lacked flavour.

Rating: 3
The best soup on this website. I tried the Ann Arbor one too and this is definitely better. I made mushroom stock from leftover stems and used it instead of water, but I did add the prescribed amount of beef stock. I agree the soup won't be a favorite if you are looking for barley flavor, but for me, it's about the mushrooms. A money saving tip: if you have an Oriental store nearby, but the shiitakes (or equivalent Chinese brown mushrooms) there instead of the regular supermarket...you'll save a lot.

