Rating: 3
Very good. I thought the recipe called for too much olive oil, so I fried three strips of bacon and used a few tablespoons of fat from that to fry the mushrooms and onions. I used beef broth instead of chicken and added about a pound of well-browned beef stew meat to the mix. I also threw in a bay leaf. My husband is not a soup or mushroom fan but he went back for seconds.

Rating: 4
Fantastic! I actually made this out of the Gourmet cookbook and everything so far has been great, this being no exception. I used beef broth (Trader Joes fat free boxed brand) instead of chicken broth as well and I found that it needed plenty of salt and pepper. Taste well and don't skimp. I also needed to add just a bit more broth at the end. Otherwise the soup is nice and earthy with just a hint of the sherry and a slight sweetness presumably from the garlic and onion. The shitakes also add great texture, and dont' leave out the parsley at the end, it adds a nice bright quality. We loved it. I halved it and it fed my SO and I (with salad and bread) for dinner plus enough for three servings of leftovers at least. I can't wait to eat them!

