Rating: 3
I usually make barley soup with beef stock. I had a lot of homemade chicken broth and decided to try this recipe. I had about 15 large fresh shitake mushrooms and used them instead of dried. Only had a few button mushrooms and threw them in. I used 10 cups of chicken broth instead of 5 broth and 5 water, as my broth was rather thin, and chopped up some celery to saute with the onions. Substituted marsala for the sherry which I was out of. Delicious and easy. Will definitely make it again.

